<subSubSection id="2FB054F6B046FFD30EBEFC1CA472FBCB" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6715077DB046FFD30EBEFC1CA472FBCB" blockId="8.[151,1436,981,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30EBEFC1CA14CFC34" bold="true" box="[151,304,981,1006]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution.</emphasis>
Most of Europe north to 
<number id="D162155AB046FFD30C76FC1CA201FC37" box="[607,637,981,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="54.0">54</number>
°N, present in 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30D0FFC1CA3FEFC37" box="[806,898,981,1005]" name="Sweden" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, absent on British Isles and Balkan Peninsula. Known from 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30F07FC30A103FBCB" box="[302,383,1017,1041]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30FA3FC30A184FBCB" box="[394,504,1017,1041]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30C07FC30A2E7FBCB" box="[558,667,1017,1041]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="033B7A8CB046FFD30C80FC30A32CFBCB" author="Westrich" box="[681,848,1017,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich 
<number id="D162155AB046FFD30D3CFC30A32CFBCB" box="[789,848,1017,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="033B7A8CB046FFD30D72FC30A47DFBCB" author="Warncke" box="[859,1025,1017,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number id="D162155AB046FFD30DECFC30A47DFBCB" box="[965,1025,1017,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2FB054F6B046FFD30EE0FBD4A4F1FAD7" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="6715077DB046FFD30EE0FBD4A4F1FAD7" blockId="8.[151,1436,981,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30EE0FBD4A155FBEC" bold="true" box="[201,297,1053,1078]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Biology.</emphasis>
Very rare species of sand dunes and larger sandy sites, in most countries known only from few records. 
<bibRefCitation id="033B7A8CB046FFD30ED0FB88A1CEFB83" author="Bluthgen" box="[249,434,1089,1113]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Bluthgen, P. (1934) Die Wirte der Palaarktischen Sphecodes - Arten. Zeitschrift Wissenschaftlicher Insekten-Biologie, 27, 33 - 42, 61 - 66. Bluthgen, P. (1935) Halictus, Nomioides und Sphecodes, pp. 360 - 367. In: Popov, V. V. (ed.) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna von Tadzhikistan. Trudy Tajikskoy Bazy Akademie Nauk SSSR, 5, 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="1934">
Blüthgen (
<number id="D162155AB046FFD30F59FB88A1D6FB83" box="[368,426,1089,1113]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1934.0">1934</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30C10FB88A3B8FB83" authority="Lepeletier" authorityName="Lepeletier" box="[569,964,1089,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30C10FB88A344FB83" box="[569,824,1089,1113]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Lasioglossum nigripes</emphasis>
(Lepeletier)
</taxonomicName>
as the likely host, but this species differs slightly in ecology. 
<bibRefCitation id="033B7A8CB046FFD30F5DFBACA255FBA7" author="Westrich" box="[372,553,1125,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich (
<number id="D162155AB046FFD30FCEFBACA25DFBA7" box="[487,545,1125,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30C87FBACA3BCFBA7" authority="Smith" authorityName="Smith" box="[686,960,1125,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30C87FBACA30AFBA7" box="[686,886,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Halictus confusus</emphasis>
Smith
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30DDEFBAFA493FBA7" authority="Rossi" authorityName="Rossi" box="[1015,1263,1125,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subauratus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30DDEFBAFA4E9FBA7" box="[1015,1173,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. subauratus</emphasis>
(Rossi)
</taxonomicName>
as likely hosts, without any evidence. In our observations, the most likely host is 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30DB3FB43A4E3FB7B" authority="Ebmer" authorityName="Ebmer" box="[922,1183,1161,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucaheneus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30DB3FB43A436FB7B" box="[922,1098,1161,1185]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. leucaheneus</emphasis>
Ebmer
</taxonomicName>
and probably also 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30BA8FB43A1E5FB1F" authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seladonius">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30BA8FB43A173FB1F" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. seladonius</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
. We collected few 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30C56FB67A37CFB1F" box="[639,768,1198,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30C56FB67A37CFB1F" box="[639,768,1198,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at places with common occurence of 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB046FFD30AE0FB67A506FB1F" box="[1225,1402,1197,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucaheneus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB046FFD30AE0FB67A506FB1F" box="[1225,1402,1197,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. leucaheneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30EBEFB18A080FB33" box="[151,252,1233,1257]" name="Slovakia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30F21FB1BA116FB30" box="[264,362,1234,1258]" name="Hungary" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hungary</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1FBD47EDB046FFD30F8BFB18A273FB33" box="[418,527,1233,1257]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and the association seems to be possible. However, the most likely host and the cleptoparasite are both rare in central Europe, and to prove the host association is difficult.
</paragraph>
